ect memories like fools collect money. Because in the end, that's all you have - happy memories.\n\n- Sarah Strohmeyer, Kindred Spirits\n|\nIn relationships, there are no beginning and no end.\n\n- Santosh\n|\nWe were all created differently, each with his/her calling and purpose\n\n- Sunday\n|\nI lean against my sister's shoulder. 'I thought lightning wasn't supposed to strike in the same place twice.''Sure it does,' Izzy tells me. 'But only if you're too dumb to move.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, My Sister's Keeper\n|\nThe story of life is quicker than the wink of an eye, the story of love is hello and goodbye...until we meet again\n\n- Jimi\n|\nA woman, especially if she have the misfortune of knowing anything, should conceal it as well as she can.\n\n- Jane\n|\nRather than love, than money, than fame, give me truth.\n\n- Henry David Thoreau, Walden\n|\nதடைகளை தாண்டிப்பார்;இன்னல்களை தளர்த்திப்பார்,வாய்ப்புகளை பயன்படுத்திப்பார்,வெற்றி கிடைக்கும், பொறுத்திருந்து பார்,திரும்பிப்பார்க்கும், பெருத்த இந்த பார்!\n\n- samura\n|\nYou will have five hundred million little bells, and I shall have five hundred million springs of fresh water...\n\n- Antoine de Saint-Exupéry, The Little Prince\n|\nShe nailed it to the wall with her well-aimed dart, like a butterfly with no will whose sentence has always been written.\n\n- Gabriel\n|\nShe's always loved writers, even more than the books I think. They're like personal friends to her.\n\n- Josephine Hart, The truth about love\n|\nWe're all a genius, but If you judge a fish by its ability to climb a tree, it will live its whole life believing that it is stupid.\n\n- Albert\n|\nTruth is like the sun. You can shut it out for a time, but it ain't going away.\n\n- Elvis\n|\n...man's life must be a straight line of motion from goal to farther goal, each leading to the next and to a single growing sum, like a journey...\n\n- Ayn Rand, Atlas Shrugged\n|\nIf you must be great, you must learn to check and compel yourself to invest time.\n\n- Sunday 